description: From Middle English osel, from Old English ōsle, from Proto-West Germanic *ą̄slā, *amslā, from Proto-Germanic *amslǭ. Cognate with German Amsel.
For the spelling, compare Early Modern English bloud (“blood”).

entries.meaning: (now regional) The Eurasian blackbird, Turdus merula.
(chiefly Canada, US) The water ouzel, an aquatic perching bird, Cinclus mexicanus.
